
fast-live-reload: The swiss army knife of live reloading.
{{GRAY}}Monitors multiple folders for changes, notifies connected clients, executes programs, serves local content, proxies sites, iframe reloads existing pages...{{RESET}}

{{BOLD}}Usage:{{RESET}} {{BLUE}}{{BINARY}} {{BOLD}}[options]{{RESET}}

{{BOLD}}Options:{{RESET}}
    {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}--interval{{RESET}}          {{GRAY}}Poll every how many milliseconds.  [100]{{RESET}}
    {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}-s{{RESET}}, {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}--serve{{RESET}}         {{GRAY}}Folder or site (via IFrame) to serve.{{RESET}}
    {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}-e{{RESET}}, {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}--execute{{RESET}}       {{GRAY}}Execute the given commands on change.{{RESET}}
    {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}-ep{{RESET}}, {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}-pe{{RESET}}, {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}--parallel-execute{{RESET}}
                        {{GRAY}}Run processes as long as fast-live-reload runs.{{RESET}}
    {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}-p{{RESET}}, {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}--port{{RESET}}          {{GRAY}}Port to listen to.  [9001]{{RESET}}
    {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}-sp{{RESET}}, {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}--serve-port{{RESET}}   {{GRAY}}Port to serve files to.  [9000]{{RESET}}
    {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}-ns{{RESET}}, {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}--no-serve{{RESET}}     {{GRAY}}Don't serve any local folder or site.{{RESET}}
    {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}-nc{{RESET}}, {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}--no-clients{{RESET}}   {{GRAY}}Don't start the client change server.{{RESET}}
    {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}-ni{{RESET}}, {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}--no-inject{{RESET}}    {{GRAY}}Don't inject client code.{{RESET}}
    {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}-nn{{RESET}}, {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}--no-notify{{RESET}}    {{GRAY}}Don't notify clients.{{RESET}}
    {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}-n{{RESET}}, {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}--dry-run{{RESET}}       {{GRAY}}Show what will be done. Don't execute.{{RESET}}
    {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}--add-path{{RESET}}          {{GRAY}}Paths to monitor for changes. Defaults to serve folder.{{RESET}}

{{BOLD}}Example:{{RESET}}
fast-live-reload {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}-s{{RESET}} {{BLUE}}/target/{{GRAY}} \\{{RESET}}
    {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}-ep{{RESET}} "{{GREEN}}tsc --watch --rootDir src/ts --outDir out/js --sourceMap src/ts/*.ts{{RESET}}"{{GRAY}}\\{{RESET}}
    {{BLUE}}{{BOLD}}-ep{{RESET}} "{{GREEN}}compass watch{{RESET}}"{{GRAY}}\\{{RESET}}
    {{BLUE}}src/js {{BOLD}}-e{{RESET}} "{{GREEN}}grunt concat sync{{RESET}}"{{GRAY}}\\{{RESET}}
    {{BLUE}}src/html src/css {{BOLD}}-e{{RESET}} "{{GREEN}}grunt sync{{RESET}}"{{RESET}}

1. Will notify the changes for clients on port {{BLUE}}9001{{RESET}}
2. and will serve the content from {{BLUE}}/target/{{RESET}} on port {{BLUE}}9000{{RESET}}
3. and will run on startup, and then kill on shutdown:
   {{GRAY}}a: {{GREEN}}tsc --watch --rootDir src/ts --outDir out/js --sourceMap src/ts/*.ts{{RESET}}
   {{GRAY}}b: {{GREEN}}compass watch{{RESET}}
4. and will monitor and execute when files change in subfolders:
   {{GRAY}}a: {{BLUE}}src/js   {{GRAY}}-> {{GREEN}}grunt concat sync{{RESET}}
   {{GRAY}}b: {{BLUE}}src/html {{GRAY}}-> {{GREEN}}grunt sync{{RESET}}
      {{BLUE}}src/css{{RESET}}
